ased on <strong>&#8220;how they sell&#8221;</strong> more than <strong>&#8220;what they are selling&#8221;</strong>&#8230; Using <a href=\"http://www.seodesignsolutions.com/\">SEO</a> is great (for a finely-tuned offer), but if there is no conversion objective, call to action or value, sending traffic (no matter how vast) is a moot point.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_7944\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\" style=\"width: 293px\"><a href=\"http://www.seodesignsolutions.com/blog/internet-marketing/squeeze-pages-and-seo/\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-7944\" title=\"squeeze-pages\" src=\"http://www.seodesignsolutions.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/squeeze-pages.jpg\" alt=\"direct-response-squeeze-pages\" width=\"283\" height=\"424\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">How Squeeze Pages Put the Squeeze on Your Wallet!</p></div>\n<h3>RULE #1:</h3>\n<p>Forget What You <strong>&#8220;THINK&#8221;</strong> you Know!<span id=\"more-7941\"></span> If you are struggling to move products or <a href=\"http://www.seodesignsolutions.com/seo-services.html\" title=\"SEO Services\">services</a> online, itâ€™s time to put your ego in the back seat, forget about what you thought works and learn (from studying) offers from real people who make a living by positioning offers for consumers-in-need and study the cues they utilize to get people to whip out their credit cards or go to Paypal and <strong>&#8220;take action&#8221;</strong> day in and day out.</p>\n<p>What tactics are prominent in the online conversion process for squeeze pages?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Benefits</li>\n<li>Value</li>\n<li>Countering Mental Objections</li>\n<li>Reinforcing their Solution</li>\n<li>Scarcity</li>\n</ul>\n<p>and other proven online tactics.</p>\n<h3>RULE #2:</h3>\n<p>Implement the <strong>&#8220;Problem/Solution, Action/Reward&#8221;</strong> Modality:  If you implement some form of online marketing on your website, there is always room for improvement. Letâ€™s use <a href=\"http://growyourmartialartsschool.com/\">http://growyourmartialartsschool.com/</a> as a case study (this is not an affiliate link) but since I used their site, the least I can do is link to it to show my appreciation for their layering process.</p>\n<p>You can learn a great deal from observing the format of <strong>&#8220;how the sell&#8221;</strong> and lead your mind through a carefully selected process until every instinct yells <strong>&#8220;buy it now&#8221;</strong>, itâ€™s a great value &#8211; if the offer (a) structured its mental argument properly (b) conveys immediate value (c) ignites your emotional impulse purchase or (d) appeals to your dilemma / circumstance &#8211; to solve your current problem.  Often, you may observe affiliate marketing employs:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A keyword rich domain.</li>\n<li>Minimal distractions for the theme (so you can focus on the offer).</li>\n<li>Proper segmentation (in this instance a martial art schools who doesnâ€™t know how to market themselves) and</li>\n<li>Have a great price point (which they can scale) 1000 conversion x $27 = more seed capital to scale using multiple sites and products on auto-pilot.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Using this example, the $27 / month (less than a coffee a day) seems like nothing compared to <strong>â€œthe value you getâ€</strong>. Disregard <strong>â€œwhat they are sellingâ€</strong> just look at <strong>â€œHowâ€</strong>.</p>\n<p>This is an excellent example of what works on the web (since you may never see that visitor again) and they emphasize scarcity, and virtually counter every assumed mental objective and win the argument in every logical compelling variable of <strong>why you should buy their solution</strong>.</p>\n<p>All that is missing is traffic (which is easy to jumpstart with PPC) when you find how your offer converts, you can spend up to Â½ of the conversion amount per day to â€œget more trafficâ€, use other affiliates if you created the offer) or target specific keywords using SEO for immediate benefit (then stem into multiple keywords over time).  Observe the action words such as:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>How to (know how)</li>\n<li>You will Receive (value-rich benefit)</li>\n<li>A 4 step process (using numbers to convey specificity) to unify the left/right brain to reinforce and emotional impulse-purchase.</li>\n<li>Act now (scarcity)</li>\n</ul>\n<div id=\"attachment_7942\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\" style=\"width: 496px\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-7942\" title=\"example-a\" src=\"http://www.seodesignsolutions.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/example-a.jpg\" alt=\"example-a\" width=\"486\" height=\"343\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">The appeal of &quot;benefits&quot; - in action</p></div>\n<p>Another example of benefit-rich intro and follow up:</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_7943\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\" style=\"width: 496px\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-7943\" title=\"example-b\" src=\"http://www.seodesignsolutions.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/example-b.jpg\" alt=\"example-b\" width=\"486\" height=\"324\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Stage 2- appealing to logic and emotion</p></div>\n<p>This is copy that sells; love it or hate it â€“ it works on a large population of those who stumble upon them.  Despite how cheesy or tacky squeeze pages seem, they work and itâ€™s not from the attractive designs they employ, it is the copy and format of the copy, the voice and the value they promise that set the tone for conversion.</p>\n<p>So, the next time you consider scoffing at one, take time to study the undertones and determine which action reward modality you can put in place for your offers.\n<div class=\"tweetmeme_button\" style=\"float: right; margin-left: 10px;\">\n			<a href=\"http://api.tweetmeme.com/share?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.seodesignsolutions.com%2Fblog%2Finternet-marketing%2Fsqueeze-pages-and-seo%2F\"><br />\n				<img src=\"http://api.tweetmeme.com/imagebutton.gif?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.seodesignsolutions.com%2Fblog%2Finternet-marketing%2Fsque