17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4853:\"<p>For those of you who didnâ€™t catch the buzz, Google is rolling out another revolutionary contribution to search called â€œ<a href=\"http://www.google.com/instant/#utm_campaign=launch&amp;utm_medium=van&amp;utm_source=instant\">Google Instant</a>â€. To summarize, just think real-time search results that refresh as you type -<strong> &#8220;without you having to click search&#8221;</strong>.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_7921\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\" style=\"width: 398px\"><a href=\"http://www.seodesignsolutions.com/blog/internet-news/google-instant-going-live-in-a-data-center-near-you/\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-7921\" title=\"google-instant-meets-caffeine\" src=\"http://www.seodesignsolutions.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/google-instant-meets-caffeine.jpg\" alt=\"Google-Instant\" width=\"388\" height=\"309\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Google Instant Meets Google Caffeine!</p></div>\n<p>This new upgrade allows you to shave seconds off your search time by rearranging the SERPs (search engine result pages) live as you are simultaneously offered suggestions on alternative keyword or key phrase variations.</p>\n<p>While the <a href=\"http://www.seodesignsolutions.com/\">SEO</a> implications have not been assessed, the ability to see what results <strong>â€œabove the foldâ€</strong> beckon you to click <strong>â€œusing this live real-time previewâ€</strong> allow you to ideally find what you need faster and more efficiently.<span id=\"more-7920\"></span></p>\n<p>While the vast implications of how this will impact search behavior are yet unknown, what is certain is that the ceaseless desire to improve upon search platforms is a constant as many Google users have survived frictional shifts as a result of transitions such as Googleâ€™s logo modifications, changes to their favicon, usability modifications (with the recent 2 column sidebar shift) and others modification are becoming commonplace to users.</p>\n<p>While we attempted to preview this feature, we had to be logged in to Google (analytics, Gmail, etc.) in order to see the <strong>â€œliveâ€</strong> results shifting about.</p>\n<p>While this may be an added benefit to many, the general consensus around the web thus far suggests that the <strong>â€œlive shiftingâ€</strong> of search results may be a bit too frantic for some and invoke the same reaction as blinking banners and other annoying on site elements.</p>\n<p>I personally enjoy the action-packed SERPs and if you know what youâ€™re looking for, you may have to take A.D.D medication to stay focused. Letâ€™s just hope it becomes an optional feature for those who like their results static or stale.</p>\n<p>Combined with <a href=\"http://www.seodesignsolutions.com/blog/search-engine-optimization/google-caffeine-site-speed-and-new-search-engine-filters/\">Google caffeine</a>, this is a one-two punch that will definitely keep the masses reeling until the novelty factor wears off.\n<div class=\"tweetmeme_button\" style=\"float: right; margin-left: 10px;\">\n			<a href=\"http://api.tweetmeme.com/share?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.seodesignsolutions.com%2Fblog%2Finternet-news%2Fgoogle-instant-going-live-in-a-data-center-near-you%2F\"><br />\n				<img src=\"http://api.tweetmeme.com/imagebutton.gif?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.seodesignsolutions.com%2Fblog%2Finternet-news%2Fgoogle-instant-going-live-in-a-data-center-near-you%2F&amp;style=normal\" height=\"61\" width=\"50\" /><br />\n			</a>\n		</div>\n\n\n<h3>Related Posts</h3>\n<ol>\n		<li><a href=\"http://www.seodesignsolutions.com/blog/internet-news/will-google-real-time-search-eclipse-the-static-web/\" rel=\"bookmark\">Will Google Real Time Search Eclipse The Static Web?</a><!-- (14.4489)--></li>\n		<li><a href=\"http://www.seodesignsolutions.com/blog/seo-basics/will-the-real-google-search-results-please-stand-up/\" rel=\"bookmark\">Will the Real Google Search Results Please Stand Up?</a><!-- (11.3532)--></li>\n		<li><a href=\"http://www.seodesignsolutions.com/blog/seo/will-caffeinated-results-from-google-stir-up-search-results/\" rel=\"bookmark\">Will Caffeinated Results from Google Stir Up Search Results?</a><!-- (10.7481)--></li>\n		<li><a href=\"http://www.seodesignsolutions.com/blog/internet-news/google-acquires-like-com-visual-search-engine/\" rel=\"bookmark\">Google Acquires Like.com Visual Search Engine</a><!-- (9.33057)--></li>\n		<li><a href=\"http://www.seodesignsolutions.com/blog/wordpress-seo/seo-ultimate-3-9/\" rel=\"bookmark\">SEO Ultimate 3.9 Adds &#8220;Instant Post Propulsion&#8221; Feature</a><!-- (9.14394)--></li>\n	</ol>\n<div class=\"feedflare\">\n<a href=\"http://feeds.seodesignsolutions.com/~ff/SeoDesignSolutionsBlog?a=29y5ZPtBGkw:hii2je_p34w:yIl2AUoC8zA\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/SeoDesignSolutionsBlog?d=yIl2AUoC8zA\" border=\"0\"></img></a>\n</div><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/SeoDesignSolutionsBlog/~4/29y5ZPtBGkw\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:105:\"http://www.seodesignsolutions.com/blog/internet-news/google-instant-going-live-in-a-data-center-near-you/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4